## Context

Split from 0279 (RDJ-26561 R&R, tracker 0274, remark R1-19): the referee
finds `climate_finance_corpus.csv` — one main-information column followed by
unstructured columns — unpleasant to explore manually. Restructuring changes
the shipped data product (column order/shape of a published Zenodo artifact
and every downstream consumer), so it is an author decision, hence
needs-human. 0279 delivers the variables table either way; this ticket
settles whether the CSV itself changes.

## Relevant files

- `climate_finance_corpus.csv` producing script (Phase-1 export; locate it)
- `scripts/schemas.py` — schema to update if columns change
- Downstream consumers of the CSV (grep before deciding blast radius)
- Ticket 0280 — Zenodo restructure; a new CSV shape must ship in the same
  new deposit version

## Actions

1. Enumerate consumers and the blast radius of a column reorder/rename.
2. Author decides: restructure (then implement, update schema + consumers +
   tests, coordinate with 0280's deposit) or keep layout and answer R1-19
   via the variables table + codebook, with the rationale in the response
   letter.

## Test

- If restructured: schema validation + downstream tests green;
  byte/content-level check of the regenerated CSV against expectations.

## Verification

- [ ] Decision recorded in the log with rationale

## Invariants

- Concept DOI stability on Zenodo; downstream pipeline unbroken.

## Exit criteria

